cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.SI 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes an AutoML based end-to-end framework for deep learning based recommender systems. It also involves the use of embedding layers, which are commonly used in deep learning models. 

It could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as recommender systems are often used in information retrieval applications. 

Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves the use of deep learning techniques for recommendation. 

The paper also involves optimization algorithms, which could place it under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). 

Finally, it could be categorized under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as recommender systems are often used in social networks and involve analyzing user/item popularity.
